aws::graph::propositions: Boeing-Stearman Model 75 Aircraft in Canada
41-8621 is a PT-17 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
41-8621 is airworthy.
41-8621 is located at the Canadian Warplane Heritage Museum.
The Canadian Warplane Heritage Museum is in Hamilton, Ontario.
42-17456 is a PT-13D Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
42-17456 is owned by Daniel Jones.
Daniel Jones is from Lacombe, Alberta.
5284 is an N2S-3 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
5284 is under restoration to airworthy condition.
5284 is with Daniel Jones of Lacombe, Alberta.
5293 is an N2S-3 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
5293 is owned by J. Kurtin.
J. Kurtin is from Collingwood, Ontario.
30083 is an N2S-4 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
30083 is on display at the Reynolds-Alberta Museum.
The Reynolds-Alberta Museum is in Wetaskiwin, Alberta.
61105 is an N2S-5 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
61105 is with Bruce Bond.
Bruce Bond is from Sarnia, Ontario.
75-3498 is a PT-17 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft.
75-3498 is airworthy.
75-3498 is owned by Great River Aviation Ltd.
Great River Aviation Ltd. is from Whitehorse, Yukon.
Great River Aviation Ltd. operates as Klondike Airways.
A PT-17 Boeing-Stearman Model 75 aircraft is registered as C-FAPG.
C-FAPG is airworthy.
C-FAPG is located at the Canadian Aviation Museum.
The Canadian Aviation Museum is in Windsor, Ontario.
